snippet.textDisplay: I think the problem the new Pixel had was that 3-4 years ago when the original Pixel came out, kind of the same with the Pixel 2, it lacked features but the software experience and camera more than made up for it. And if you could sacrifice on the few features it missed, it was easily the best Android experience. But since then, things have really come a long way. The software can't carry the phone with things like Oxygen OS being as good as it is now. So lacking on the features and the software not being THAT much better than the competition kind of holds it back. It's kind of in the same space as Macs were up until very recently with the new MBP
snippet.textOriginal: I think the problem the new Pixel had was that 3-4 years ago when the original Pixel came out, kind of the same with the Pixel 2, it lacked features but the software experience and camera more than made up for it.
